title: Flying into a THUNDERSTORM in Microsoft Flight Simulator! CJ4 to Chicago O'Hare (VATSIM)

media:group.media:title: Flying into a THUNDERSTORM in Microsoft Flight Simulator! CJ4 to Chicago O'Hare (VATSIM)
media:group.media:description:
Damn virtual nature, you scary
• FS Academy: https://www.fsacademy.co.uk

Departing the Oshkosh Wittman Reg'l Airport (KOSH) for a flight to Chicago O'Hare (KORD) in the Cessna Citation CJ4. We max climb the takeoff and fly directly into a massive thunderstorm before breaking out at minimums on an ILS approach runway 28C. We park at the cargo ramp and offload our special freight delivery.
